  "prompt": "What is a list of formula sheets for each subject for the GATE in mechanical to cope with last minute preparation?",
  "response": "The Graduate Aptitude Test in Engineering (GATE) is an important exam for engineering graduates, including those in mechanical engineering. Having a list of formula sheets can be very helpful for last-minute preparation. Below is a categorized list of essential formula sheets by subject for GATE Mechanical Engineering:\n\n### 1. **Engineering Mechanics**\n   - Equations of motion (kinematics)\n   - Free-body diagrams\n   - Equilibrium conditions\n   - Work-Energy principle\n   - Impulse and momentum\n   - Centroid and center of gravity\n\n### 2. **Strength of Materials**\n   - Stress and strain definitions\n   - Bending stress and shear stress formulas\n   - Mohr's Circle theory\n   - Torsion formulas\n   - Buckling of columns\n   - Deflection in beams (moment-area and conjugate beam method)\n\n### 3. **Theory of Machines**\n   - Kinematic chains, links, and mechanisms\n   - Velocity and acceleration analysis methods (Gruebler\u2019s equation)\n   - Cam profiles (types and equations)\n   - Gear mechanisms and gear ratios\n   - Laws of machines (Virtual Work)\n\n### 4. **Machine Design**\n   - Key design formulas (factors of safety, fatigue, and wear)\n   - Failure theories (maximum stress, maximum strain)\n   - Design of shafts, beams, and bolts\n   - Design of different types of gears and cams\n   - Bearings (types and selection criteria)\n\n### 5. **Thermodynamics**\n   - Laws of thermodynamics\n   - Ideal gas laws and equations\n   - Heat engines and refrigeration cycles\n   - Entropy calculations\n   - Psychometric processes\n\n### 6. **Fluid Mechanics**\n   - Bernoulli\u2019s equation\n   - Continuity equation\n   - Viscosity and flow types\n   - Reynolds number significance\n   - Dimensional analysis and similarity\n\n### 7. **Heat Transfer**\n   - Modes of heat transfer: conduction, convection, radiation\n   - Fourier's law\n   - Newton\u2019s law of cooling\n   - Heat exchanger effectiveness\n   - Rate of heat transfer equations\n\n### 8. **Manufacturing Engineering**\n   - Processes (casting, shaping, machining)\n   - Machinability parameters\n   - Tolerances and fits\n   - Manufacturing metrics (CNC, HMC, LMC)\n   - Welding types and advantages\n\n### 9. **Industrial Engineering**\n   - Work study and time study basics\n   - Lean manufacturing principles\n   - Queuing theory basics\n   - Inventory management (EOQ and safety stock)\n   - Six Sigma basics\n\n### 10. **Engineering Ethics and Safety**\n   - Codes of ethics (for engineers)\n   - Safety protocols and hazard identification\n   - Environmental ethics\n\n### Additional Resources:\n- **Mathematics and Numerical Methods:** Important theorems, integration and differentiation formulas, numerical methods for solving equations.\n- **Control Systems:** Transfer functions, block diagrams, stability criteria, and root locus.\n\n### Tips for Last Minute Preparation:\n1. **Summarize Key Formulas:** Create condensed versions for quicker review.\n2. **Practice Problems:** Focus on high-yield problems that integrate multiple concepts.\n3. **Revise Regularly:** Cycle through subjects multiple times in the lead-up to the exam.\n\nBy organizing your formula sheets according to the subjects listed above, you can efficiently review and prepare for the GATE exam in mechanical engineering.",
